# Git Workflow

## Never commit directly to `main` without explicit user request

- **NEVER** run `git push origin main` unless the user explicitly asks to push to main
- **NEVER** run `git merge ... main` or `git checkout main && git merge` unless the user asks to merge into main
- **NEVER** commit on `main` directly — always work on a feature/fix branch

## Correct flow

1. Create a branch: `git checkout -b <branch-name>`
2. Make changes and commit on the branch
3. **Ask the user** before merging into `main` or pushing to remote
4. Only merge/push after explicit confirmation: _"merge into main"_, _"push"_, _"deploy"_

## Branch naming

- `deps/<package>` — dependency upgrades
- `fix/<description>` — bug fixes
- `feat/<description>` — new features
- `docs/<description>` — documentation

## Commits

- Commit only when the user explicitly asks
- Use concise, meaningful commit messages in English
- Never amend pushed commits
